{RAILWAYS}
Although this area is crossed by the Southern Region railway from London to Leatherhead, Dorking and Worthing, it does not have a station.
The stations of Ashtead just south of the area, Leatherhead to the south-west and Epsom to the east, all provide good services for commuters to London. Much of the housing, especially that in Epsom and Ashtead to the South and East of the area, has been developed with the commuter in mind and was built in the 1930's when fast frequent services to London meant that people could live further out of town in or near the country.
